<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 04 at 7:43PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of Harmon, northwestern
Greer, southwestern Beckham and northwestern Hardeman Counties
through 815 PM CDT...
At 743 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking the leading edge of winds
from strong thunderstorms along a line extending from 8 miles north
of Vinson to 11 miles south of Hollis. Movement was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Hollis, Gould, Vinson, Madge and McKnight.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
